</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C2998FFD3801CFF50F83F2B11FDD4" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF50F83F28BDF81A" blockId="2.[151,1436,1937,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFF50F83F2B2EF842" bold="true" box="[151,274,1937,1963]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD3801BFE54F83C28A5F842" authority="Silva-Neto" authorityName="Silva-Neto" box="[403,665,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFE54F83C282AF842" box="[403,534,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">E. atlantica</emphasis>
Silva-Neto
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the shape of the mesal endophallic sclerite, by the shape of the apical processes of the lateral endophallic sclerites (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFC6CF81B29C6F826" box="[939,1018,1973,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) and by the posterior processes of the central sclerite of the hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFDE7F8772848F81A" box="[544,628,2009,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF092A9BFFD2801AFF50F8D02E33F834" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" startId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" targetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD2801AFF50F8D02E33F834" blockId="3.[151,1437,1918,2014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD2801AFF50F8D02B06F87F" bold="true" box="[151,314,1918,1942]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">FIGURES 1–6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD2801AFEF8F8D02869F87F" authority="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete, 2022" authorityName="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete" authorityYear="2022" box="[319,597,1918,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guticortesorum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD2801AFEF8F8D02869F87F" box="[319,597,1918,1942]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Euplocania guticortesorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD2801AFD9DF8D028AFF87F" bold="true" box="[602,659,1918,1942]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2311B7AFFD2801AFD9DF8D028AFF87F" box="[602,659,1918,1942]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD5801DFF00FF382BF0FEF4" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD5801DFF00FF382B37FF59" bold="true" box="[199,267,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Color</emphasis>
(in parts mounted on slide). Head brown, with pattern of dark spots like a mask; dark brown compounds eyes; ocelli hyaline, with ochre centripetal crescents; anteclypeus and clypeus dark brown; genae dark brown. Forewings as in group diagnosis. Hypandrium brown. Phallosome brown, endophallic sclerites dark brown. Epiproct and paraprocts light brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF092A9BFFD5801DFF50F8DF2860F844" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" startId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" targetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD5801DFF50F8DF2860F844" blockId="4.[151,1437,1905,1965]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD5801DFF50F8DF2B75F860" bold="true" box="[151,329,1905,1929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">FIGURES 7–11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD5801DFE95F8DF2824F860" authority="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete, 2022" authorityName="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete" authorityYear="2022" box="[338,536,1905,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD5801DFE95F8DF2824F860" box="[338,536,1905,1929]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Euplocania wilsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD5801DFDE5F8DF2862F860" bold="true" box="[546,606,1905,1929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2311B7AFFD5801DFDE5F8DF2862F860" box="[546,606,1905,1929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD4801CFF00FF392B11FDD4" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD4801CFF00FF392B67FF58" bold="true" box="[199,347,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Morphology</emphasis>
. As in diagnosis, plus the following: Head: H/MxW: 1.48; compound eyes large, H/D: 2.11; IO/ MxW: 0.67. Outer cusp of lacinial tips with seven denticles. Forewings: pterostigma: lp/wp: 6.11. Central sclerite of the hypandrium, as in diagnosis of the group, anteriorly slightly convex; basal section wider than long, posterolateral angle with short rounded processes, with several macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD4801CFC6AFEAD2E3EFEF4" box="[941,1026,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Phallosome: side struts U-shaped; external parameres narrow, with pores; anterior pair of endophallic sclerites transverse, with short process apically, ends almost converging mesally (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD4801CFDC8FEE5285DFE8C" box="[527,609,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); lateral pair laminar, basally partially overlapping anterior sclerites, with concave laminar and semioval process apically, clearly widened; mesal sclerite inverted U-shaped, postero-mesal sclerites elongate, narrow, sinuous, distally acuminate, each connected to the external parameres (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD4801CFB31FE3D2F76FE44" box="[1270,1354,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts ovoid, with a dense field of setae on distal area, an apically spatulate macrosetae near the inner margin (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD4801CFAA8FE192A9BFE1C" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); sensory fields with 32 trichobothria on basal rosettes. Epiproct semioval (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD4801CFBCBFE752E6EFE1C" box="[1036,1106,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="134">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), with meso-anterior field of microspines on basal area and triangular bulge, bearing two setae, two lateral macrosetae and small scattered setae as illustrated.
</paragraph>
